# hermes-hub:14b — Nous Hermes 4 14B preset for the local Mac.
# Build with: ollama create hermes-hub:14b -f Modelfile.hermes-hub.14b

FROM hermes4:14b

# Hermes 4 uses ChatML. The tags below keep generation clean when the
# model emits tool calls or finishes a turn.
PARAMETER stop "<|im_end|>"
PARAMETER stop "</tool_call>"
PARAMETER stop "</tools>"
# Hermes 4 reasoning mode emits <think>...</think> blocks. The stop
# token is intentionally NOT included for </think> so reasoning streams
# through and clients can strip it if they want.

PARAMETER num_ctx 16384
PARAMETER temperature 0.6
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.05

SYSTEM """You are the local hub agent on an always-on MacBook Pro,
paired with a DGX Spark for heavy inference. You are steerable and do
not refuse reasonable requests. Be concise; prefer concrete actions and
code.

To enable extended reasoning, the caller may prepend:
  You are a deep thinking AI; enclose internal monologue within
  <think>...</think> tags before answering.

You can call tools when the caller provides a <tools>...</tools> block.
Emit calls as <tool_call>{"name": "...", "arguments": {...}}</tool_call>
and wait for a <tool_response> before answering the user."""
